vruNetwork.name: vruNetwork

revisions.description: Changed notifyAlarmByComponent, componentEventsGroup, componentNotificationsGroup, and vruNetworkMIBComplianceByComponent status to deprecated. Added notifyAlarmByComponentEx, alrmLogComponentIpAddress, componentEventsGroup2, componentNotificationsGroup2, and vruNetworkMIBComplianceByComponent2.

The component model has changed. The component id must be unique for all components of the same type. We no longer need to use IP (componentIpAddress) as the index into ComponentTable. alrmLogComponentIpAddress has been deleted and removed from notifyAlarmByComponent.

Removed VAS support (vasTable and notifyVasStateChg). Added support for components. Change alrmLogVruId, notifyVruStateChg, notifyAlarm, vruEventsGroup and vruNotificationsGroup status to deprecated. Added alrmLogComponentId, alrmLogComponentIpAddress, alrmLogComponentType, notifyAlarmByComp, componentEventsGroup, vruNetworkMIBComplianceByComponent, and componentNotificationsGroup,
Mod alrmLogMax description to be more clearer. Mod description of lineState.

Mods so SMICng does not complain. remove unused imports from IMPORTS section make MODULE-IDENTITY first entry. remove - from enum constants since this is only valid in SMIv1. add enterprises, IpAddress to imports. add size restriction to DisplayStrings used as implied index. Index item cant have size of zero. mod evtObjectId and evChange MAX-ACCESS to accessible-for-notify. add OBJECT-GROUP, NOTIFICATION-GROUP, MODULE-COMPLIANCE.
Added vruLineCnt, vruSpanCnt, vruHostCnt and hostLuCnt.

evObjectId.name: evObjectId
evObjectId.description: Object identifier associated with the source of the trap. This object can not be retrieved from the SNMP agent.

evChange.name: evChange
evChange.description: Describes the type of change which just occurred. This object can not be retrieved from the SNMP agent.

notifyAlarm.name: notifyAlarm
notifyAlarm.description: When a exceptional condition occurs the VRU system will generate an alarm. This trap forwards these alarms to the Network Management Station. **NOTE: this trap is deprecated and replaced by notifyAlarmByComponent trap

notifyVruStateChg.name: notifyVruStateChg
notifyVruStateChg.description: This trap is forwarded to the Network Management Station when the VRU changes its state. **NOTE: this trap is deprecated and replaced by the notifyComponentStateChg trap.

notifyLineAppStateChg.name: notifyLineAppStateChg
notifyLineAppStateChg.description: This trap is forwarded to the Network Management Station when a application attached to a VRU line changes its state.

notifySpanStateChg.name: notifySpanStateChg
notifySpanStateChg.description: This trap is forwarded to the Network Management Station when a VRU span changes its state.

notifyHostStateChg.name: notifyHostStateChg
notifyHostStateChg.description: This trap is forwarded to the Network Management Station when a VRU host changes its state.

notifyLuStateChg.name: notifyLuStateChg
notifyLuStateChg.description: This trap is forwarded to the Network Management Station when a VRU host lu changes its state.

notifyTopologyChg.name: notifyTopologyChg
notifyTopologyChg.description: This trap is forwarded to the Network Management Station when a VRU Network object topology status has changed.

notifyComponentStateChg.name: notifyComponentStateChg
notifyComponentStateChg.description: This trap is forwarded to the Network Management Station when a VRU Network component changes its state.

notifyAlarmByComponent.name: notifyAlarmByComponent
notifyAlarmByComponent.description: When a exceptional condition occurs the VPS/is network a component will generate an alarm. This trap forwards these these alarms to the Network Management Station. **NOTE: this trap is deprecated and replaced by the notifyAlarmByComponentEx trap.

notifyAlarmByComponentEx.name: notifyAlarmByComponentEx
notifyAlarmByComponentEx.description: When a exceptional condition occurs the VPS/is network a component will generate an alarm. This trap forwards these these alarms to the Network Management Station. This is an extended version of notifyAlarmByComponent and includes the IP address of the component generating the alarm.

alrmLogMax.name: alrmLogMax
alrmLogMax.description: Specifies the maximum number of alarms that may be logged in the alarm log table at once. When alrmLogNumber is equivalent to alrmLogMax, the first alarm in the table will be removed when the next alarm is added.

alrmLogNumber.name: alrmLogNumber
alrmLogNumber.description: The number of log entries currently defined.

alrmLogTable.name: alrmLogTable
alrmLogTable.description: A list of alarm entries. The number of entries is given by alrmLogNumber. This list could be thought of as a queue. When the comonent generates an alarm, it is added to the end of the list. If the number of entries reaches alrmLogMax than the first entry will be deleted before a new one is added.

alrmLogTableEntry.name: alrmLogTableEntry
alrmLogTableEntry.description: An alarm entry containing objects that describe that alarm.

alrmLogIdx.name: alrmLogIdx
alrmLogIdx.description: Index into the alarm log table between one and alrmLogNumber.

alrmLogSeverity.name: alrmLogSeverity
alrmLogSeverity.description: Integer describing how severe this alarm is. The lower the value, the lower the severity. A severity value of 0 indicates that no severity has been assigned to this alarm.

alrmLogCode.name: alrmLogCode
alrmLogCode.description: Code assigned to identify this alarm.

alrmLogVruId.name: alrmLogVruId
alrmLogVruId.description: VRU identifier which generated this alarm. A value of 0 is used to indicate no VRU is associated with this alarm. **NOTE: this object is deprecated and has been replaced by alrmLogComponentId object.

alrmLogLineId.name: alrmLogLineId
alrmLogLineId.description: The phone line number associated with this alarm. A value of 0 indicates no phone line.

alrmLogHostId.name: alrmLogHostId
alrmLogHostId.description: The host identifier associated with this alarm. A value of 0 indicates that no host is associated with this alarm.

alrmLogProcName.name: alrmLogProcName
alrmLogProcName.description: The name of the process that generated this alarm.

alrmLogMessage.name: alrmLogMessage
alrmLogMessage.description: A message describing the alarm that occurred.

alrmLogTime.name: alrmLogTime
alrmLogTime.description: The time that this alarm was generated.

alrmLogComponentType.name: alrmLogComponentType
alrmLogComponentType.description: Component type of the VPS/is component which generated this alarm.

alrmLogComponentId.name: alrmLogComponentId
alrmLogComponentId.description: Component identifier of the VPS/is component which generated this alarm.

alrmLogComponentIpAddress.name: alrmLogComponentIpAddress
alrmLogComponentIpAddress.description: Component IP address of the VPS/is component which generated this alarm.

vruTable.name: vruTable
vruTable.description: All Voice Response Units(VRU) a agent knows about

vruTableEntry.name: vruTableEntry
vruTableEntry.description: A (conceptual) row entry for one VRU.

vruId.name: vruId
vruId.description: The VRU number associated with this VRU entity. Note that is a unique number within VRU network.

vruDescr.name: vruDescr
vruDescr.description: A textual description of this VRU entity. It is mandatory that this contain only printable ASCII characters.

vruLineCnt.name: vruLineCnt
vruLineCnt.description: Number of physical phone lines on this system.

vruSpanCnt.name: vruSpanCnt
vruSpanCnt.description: Number of spans on this system. This also indicates the number of rows in the spanTable(4) for this VRU.

vruHostCnt.name: vruHostCnt
vruHostCnt.description: Number of hosts defined for this system. This also indicates the number of rows in the hostTable(6) for this VRU.

vruAdminState.name: vruAdminState
vruAdminState.description: The network managers desired state of this VRU entity.

vruState.name: vruState
vruState.description: The current status of the VRU entity.

vruStateLastChange.name: vruStateLastChange
vruStateLastChange.description: Date and time that this VRU entity changed its state.

lineTable.name: lineTable
lineTable.description: All physical and logical lines that are attached to a Voice Response Units(VRU).

lineTableEntry.name: lineTableEntry
lineTableEntry.description: A (conceptual) entry for one physical/logical line.

lineVruId.name: lineVruId
lineVruId.description: The VRU identifier that this phone line is associated with.

lineId.name: lineId
lineId.description: The line number of this phone line. This number is unique for each VRU.

lineType.name: lineType
lineType.description: Specifies whether this line is a logical(3) or a physical(4) phone line. A line type of unknown(2) indicates that we cant determine the line type at this moment.

lineProtocol.name: lineProtocol
lineProtocol.description: A value which indicates the set of protocols this phone line offers. The value is a sum. This value initially takes the value of zero which indicates that the protocol is unknown. Then for each protocol that this line supports, its protocol value is added to the sum. Value Functionality 0x00001 Uses some other type of protocol 0x00002 Some analog protocol 0x00004 AT&T Bell release 0x00008 British Paging (BTUK/MCP) 0x00010 Channel bank with 2 wire option 0x00020 Channel bank with 2 wire FXOR else FXO 0x00040 Channel bank with 4 wire E&M 0x00080 Channel bank FSX[r] else FXO[R] 0x00100 Channel bank loop start else ground 0x00200 Channel bank standard access 0x00400 Common channel signalling (SS7) 0x00800 Galaxy 5/2 ACD 0x01000 ISDN 0x02000 Loop hangup supervision 0x04000 Mercury CAS signalling 0x08000 Network side protocol 0x10000 R1 signaling system 0x20000 R2 signaling with DTMF outdial 0x40000 R2 signaling system

lineState.name: lineState
lineState.description: Current state of this line. The line may be currently servicing a call (connected), in service but not in a call service or referral state (idle), not in service nor down (busy), referral (referral), or down (down). If we are unable to connect to the VRU than the line state will be unknown (unknown). A logical line line state will always be unknown.

lineAppName.name: lineAppName
lineAppName.description: The name of the application that is currently assigned to this line. Any response PDU on this object will return the name of the application assigned to this line. If there is no application assigned to this line, a 0 length string is returned. Assigning a new application to this line is achieved by setting lineAppAdminState to assign and this object to the applications name.

lineAppOverlay.name: lineAppOverlay
lineAppOverlay.description: The name of the application that has been linked to this line.

lineAppAdminState.name: lineAppAdminState
lineAppAdminState.description: Desired state that Network Manager wants the application in.

lineAppState.name: lineAppState
lineAppState.description: Current state of the application that is assigned to this logical line. If no applications are assigned this entry will be noapp(3)

lineAppStateLastChange.name: lineAppStateLastChange
lineAppStateLastChange.description: Date and time that the current application assigned to this line last changed its state.

lineAppCfgLastChange.name: lineAppCfgLastChange
lineAppCfgLastChange.description: Date and time of last application configure or unconfigure on this line.

spanTable.name: spanTable
spanTable.description: All spans which are attached to a Voice Response Unit (VRU).

spanVruId.name: spanVruId
spanVruId.description: VRU identifier that this span is associated with.

spanLineIdStart.name: spanLineIdStart
spanLineIdStart.description: Line id of the first line in this span.

spanLineNumber.name: spanLineNumber
spanLineNumber.description: Number of lines in this span.

spanEnabled.name: spanEnabled
spanEnabled.description: Indicates whether span is enabled or disabled. A value of true(1) indicates span is enabled and a value of false(2) indicates span is disabled.

spanStateLastChange.name: spanStateLastChange
spanStateLastChange.description: Date and time that the span last changed its state.

appTable.name: appTable
appTable.description: All applications that VRU currently knows about.

appTableEntry.name: appTableEntry
appTableEntry.description: A (conceptual) entry for one VRU application

appVruId.name: appVruId
appVruId.description: VRU id that this application has been assigned to.

appName.name: appName
appName.description: The name of the application that can been assigned to a line. This name must be unique for each VRU

appDescr.name: appDescr
appDescr.description: A textual description of this application. It is mandatory that this contain only printable ASCII characters.

appOptions.name: appOptions
appOptions.description: The options that are needed during this applications startup.

appLineCnt.name: appLineCnt
appLineCnt.description: The number of lines that this application is assigned to.

appStatsTable.name: appStatsTable
appStatsTable.description: All application specific stats that have been collected.

appStatsTableEntry.name: appStatsTableEntry
appStatsTableEntry.description: A (conceptual) entry for one application stat

appStatsVruId.name: appStatsVruId
appStatsVruId.description: The VRU identifier that this application statistic is associated with.

appStatsName.name: appStatsName
appStatsName.description: Name which identifies this application stat.

appStatsValue.name: appStatsValue
appStatsValue.description: An application stats value. This value is gathered on 15 minute intervals.

appStatsLastChange.name: appStatsLastChange
appStatsLastChange.description: Date and time when this application stat was recorded.

hostTable.name: hostTable
hostTable.description: All hosts defined for a VRU.

hostTableEntry.name: hostTableEntry
hostTableEntry.description: A (conceptual) entry for one VRU host

hostVruId.name: hostVruId

hostDescr.name: hostDescr

hostLuCnt.name: hostLuCnt

hostProtocol.name: hostProtocol

hostMedia.name: hostMedia

hostAdminState.name: hostAdminState

hostStateLastChange.name: hostStateLastChange

luVruId.name: luVruId

luHostId.name: luHostId
luHostId.description: Host entity that this LU is associated with.

luId.name: luId
luId.description: LU identifier that is associated with this LU.

luDescr.name: luDescr
luDescr.description: A textual description of this LU. It is mandatory that this contain only printable ASCII characters.

luPoolName.name: luPoolName
luPoolName.description: Pool name that this LU is assigned to.

luStateLastChange.name: luStateLastChange
luStateLastChange.description: Date and time this lu last changed it state.

componentTypeTableEntry.name: componentTypeTableEntry
componentTypeTableEntry.description: A (conceptual) entry for one component type.

componentTable.name: componentTable
componentTable.description: All components found in the system.

componentStateLastChange.name: componentStateLastChange
componentStateLastChange.description: Date and time this component last changed its state.
